e run, it could cause failures, but using getBundle might catch exceptions if the pattern is covered. If the resource isn’t included, it can negatively impact assertions. I’m considering whether to create a ListResourceBundle or if the properties resource could be automatically included.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring version-agnostic testing**\\n\\nI need to ensure my tests are version-agnostic. I can test for a missing bundle path by calling getBundle and catching any exceptions that come up, logging the formatted key when necessary. If ResourceBundle.getBundle is called with a nonexistent path, a MissingResourceException will be caught. This way, I can still cover the call site even if the resource is missing. It seems the Graal agent logs ResourceBundle access mainly when it’s successful, so I'm curious about tracking coverage on dynamic access and actual outcomes.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_k1C98jL7twSz7LOASDhqC72K|fc_0bedce73ea0a9a220169fba60ed84881939a303ff34307cec8", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find build -type f \\( -name '*dynamic*' -o -name '*coverage*' -o -name '*.json' \\) | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 745, "output": 870, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20047, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778099710718, "responseId": "resp_0bedce73ea0a9a220169fba5ff5a408193939e45348921c849"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_k1C98jL7twSz7LOASDhqC72K|fc_0bedce73ea0a9a220169fba60ed84881939a303ff34307cec8", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "build/discovered-artifact-metadata/ch.qos.reload4j-reload4j-1.2.19.json\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778099727252}]}
